, he was named to the <team wordnetid="108208560" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../270/4119270.xml">
United States national baseball team</link></team>
 for the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../745/77745.xml">
2008 Olympics</link> in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../746/18603746.xml">
Beijing</link></village>
.</p>
<p>

In ten seasons in the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../148/20148.xml">
minor leagues</link> through <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../405/13639405.xml">
2008</link>, he was <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../785/300785.xml">
26</link>-<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../090/6969090.xml">
18</link> with 63 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../345/313345.xml">
saves</link> and a 3.09 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../825/101825.xml">
ERA</link> in 340 games.</p>
<p>

Koplove thows with a different arm angle than most pitchers. His arm angle is perpendicular to his body which inturn allows his <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../802/467802.xml">
fastball</link> to sink and his <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../830/467830.xml">
curveball</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../819/467819.xml">
slider</link> to stay on the same plane making it appear to be a fastball.</p>

